{"id":6146,"date":"2024-06-11T10:00:00","date_gmt":"2024-06-11T04:30:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/?p=6146"},"modified":"2024-06-15T16:44:06","modified_gmt":"2024-06-15T11:14:06","slug":"fun-and-easy-summer-decor-ideas","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/fun-and-easy-summer-decor-ideas\/","title":{"rendered":"8 Breezy Summer Decoration Ideas for Your Home Sweet Home"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Summer decoration that blends age-old wisdom with modern solutions ahead. Click now!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Summers in India have always been intense, but in the past, our ancestors had some ingenious strategies to keep homes cool and comfortable. Today, we face new challenges\u2014traffic, pollution, work stress, and unhealthy habits\u2014especially as we spend more time indoors since the pandemic.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>This blog explores how we can blend age-old wisdom with modern solutions to create a peaceful, cool haven in our homes this summer. Let\u2019s dive into these eight summer decoration ideas!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Summer Decoration With Fresh Greens<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>In the past, Indian homes often featured wide courtyards and lush green surroundings, offering a naturally cooling space. Today, while space and pollution limit our outdoor forays, we can still incorporate the easiest <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-decor\/\">home decor<\/a> for summers- the plants, into our homes in the form of biophilic interiors. Adding potted plants, vertical gardens, and indoor trees not only cools the air through its evaporation element but also enhances air quality and creates a soothing ambience.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191444\/summer-decoration-with-green-plants.jpg\" alt=\"Summer decoration incorporate plants in the form of biophilic interiors\" class=\"wp-image-56979\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191444\/summer-decoration-with-green-plants.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191444\/summer-decoration-with-green-plants-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191444\/summer-decoration-with-green-plants-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191444\/summer-decoration-with-green-plants-50x30.jpg 50w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191444\/summer-decoration-with-green-plants-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Plants &#8211; Most affordable summer decoration for home<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Explore perfect indoor plants for home here: <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-decor\/air-purifying-indoor-plants\/\">Air Purifying Indoor Plants<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Home Decor for Summer: Light &amp; Airy Fabrics&nbsp;<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Traditionally, homes used materials like jute and khus to shield windows and keep interiors cool. In modern home interiors, you can opt for light colours and breathable fabrics like cotton and linen curtains, cushions and throws. These allow for better airflow, and with some floral room freshener, you have a fresh and relaxed space to retreat.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191425\/home-decor-for-summer.jpg\" alt=\"Home decor for summer: Choose light colours and breathable fabrics, such as cotton and linen curtains, cushions, and throws\" class=\"wp-image-56977\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191425\/home-decor-for-summer.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191425\/home-decor-for-summer-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191425\/home-decor-for-summer-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191425\/home-decor-for-summer-50x30.jpg 50w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191425\/home-decor-for-summer-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Choose pastel fabrics for summer<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Get a Free Modular Kitchen Worth \u20b92 Lakhs with Your Home Interiors.\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/08183703\/designcafe-offer-free-modular-kitchen-worth-2-lakhs.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Summer Season Decoration Ideas: Go Minimal&nbsp;<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Do you remember how our traditional Indian homes had big courtyards for people to wind down? With space constraints in present times, Indian homeowners should focus on <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/minimalist-home-design-ideas\/\">minimalistic home interiors<\/a>, especially as a summer season decoration hack. Decluttering and arranging furniture strategically will create ventilation and allow spaces to breathe. Just like a hotel lobby, let your living room breathe by removing additional items and opting for space-saving furniture.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Check out DesignCafe\u2019s space-saving interiors that guarantee 20% extra space.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191516\/summer-season-decoration-ideas.jpg\" alt=\"Summer season decoration ideas involve decluttering and strategically arranging furniture to create ventilation and open space\" class=\"wp-image-56982\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191516\/summer-season-decoration-ideas.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191516\/summer-season-decoration-ideas-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191516\/summer-season-decoration-ideas-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191516\/summer-season-decoration-ideas-50x30.jpg 50w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191516\/summer-season-decoration-ideas-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Decluttering is the ultimate hack for the summer season<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Summer Home Decor Ideas for a Vacation Home&nbsp;<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>We know you miss the childhood summer vacations! While we can\u2019t bring you the beach, we can make your home feel like a retreat. Not just plants, but bring in a cosy hammock or a swing chair into your balcony, and set up a burbling small water body near your main door in the form of a water fountain or an aquarium. It\u2019s time to get into those comfy cotton clothes and read your favourite book as the sun sets.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191526\/summer-theme-decoration-for-vaction-homes.jpg\" alt=\"Summer theme decoration: add a cosy hammock or a swing chair to make your home feel like a retreat\" class=\"wp-image-56983\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191526\/summer-theme-decoration-for-vaction-homes.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191526\/summer-theme-decoration-for-vaction-homes-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191526\/summer-theme-decoration-for-vaction-homes-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191526\/summer-theme-decoration-for-vaction-homes-50x30.jpg 50w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191526\/summer-theme-decoration-for-vaction-homes-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Hammock fan? Add to the cart now!<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Summer Decor Ideas Using Natural Materials<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Decades ago, or even today, homes in some places were made of clay and bamboo, which have natural thermal properties. Start integrating furniture and summer decor made of bamboo, stone, wood, and clay, which brings in the retreat vibe and gives your home a very earthy touch. You can choose a wooden bookshelf, a unique bamboo partition, rattan furniture, and much more!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191434\/indian-summer-decor-with-natural-materials.jpg\" alt=\"Indian summer decor with bamboo, stone, wood, and clay furniture creates a tranquil atmosphere\" class=\"wp-image-56978\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191434\/indian-summer-decor-with-natural-materials.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191434\/indian-summer-decor-with-natural-materials-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191434\/indian-summer-decor-with-natural-materials-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191434\/indian-summer-decor-with-natural-materials-50x30.jpg 50w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191434\/indian-summer-decor-with-natural-materials-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Opt for eco-friendly materials for home interiors<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Check out eco-friendly home interiors here: <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/sustainable-interior-design-ideas\/\">Sustainable Interior Design Ideas<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Summer Room Decor to Amp up the Cosiness&nbsp;<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Summer vacations at home mean long movie hours, ordering in, and sleeping late! You will naturally want your room to feel cool and cosy. Start by adding lots of fluffy cushions; the more, the better! Use pastel tones for bedsheets to create a soft, calming atmosphere. Let natural light seep in with sheer curtains that allow sunlight while maintaining privacy. Use candles and diffusers with summery scents like coconut and marine for a refreshing ambience. Consider bringing in a lovely bookshelf for those peaceful book-reading hours.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191505\/summer-room-decor.jpg\" alt=\"Summer room decor: Add many fluffy cushions to create a relaxed and cosy feeling\" class=\"wp-image-56981\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191505\/summer-room-decor.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191505\/summer-room-decor-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191505\/summer-room-decor-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191505\/summer-room-decor-50x30.jpg 50w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191505\/summer-room-decor-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Your bedroom, your way this summer<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Looking for interiors that inspire you?\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/12\/20180213\/looking-for-interiors-that-inspire-you.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Summer Kitchen Decor for Culinary Adventures&nbsp;<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>In the past, kitchens were often set up away from the living room to keep the heat and smell away. Today, homes must incorporate specific strategies to keep kitchens cool and functional, especially during summer. Opt for neutral-coloured cabinets to achieve a minimalistic look that reflects light and maintains a cooler environment. Installing an exhaust fan is essential to discard hot air and improve ventilation.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Additionally, consider bringing in <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/modular-kitchen-interiors\/kitchen-garden-ideas\/\">kitchen gardens<\/a> or growing natural herbs to create a fresh ambience in the kitchen. These small changes can make your kitchen a comfortable and pleasant space to cook in during the hot summer months.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191455\/summer-kitchen-interior-decor.jpg\" alt=\"Summer kitchen interior decor for culinary adventures\" class=\"wp-image-56980\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191455\/summer-kitchen-interior-decor.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191455\/summer-kitchen-interior-decor-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191455\/summer-kitchen-interior-decor-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191455\/summer-kitchen-interior-decor-50x30.jpg 50w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191455\/summer-kitchen-interior-decor-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Cool &amp; functional summer kitchens are in demand<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Fun Summer Decor to Brighten up Your Home&nbsp;<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>While we have covered the essentials, it would be a sin not to bring in some funky summer decor ideas. If one wall has been empty and plain for a long time, it\u2019s time to get a beach-inspired painting to liven it up. Consider adding a seashell decor piece for the coffee table to evoke coastal vibes. Use mirrors and opt for glossy finishes so the natural light reflects, making your home feel bigger and more spacious. And nothing beats bringing in a summer-scented diffuser; step into a house that feels refreshing and invigorating every time.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191415\/fun-summer-season-decoration.jpg\" alt=\"Summer season decoration beach-inspired painting to liven it up\" class=\"wp-image-56976\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191415\/fun-summer-season-decoration.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191415\/fun-summer-season-decoration-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191415\/fun-summer-season-decoration-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191415\/fun-summer-season-decoration-50x30.jpg 50w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/01\/11191415\/fun-summer-season-decoration-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Ace the summer decor with our handy tips and tricks\n<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If your plans for summer include a new home, don\u2019t forget to explore DesignCafe\u2019s affordable home interiors. Our designs are modern and stylish and come with up to a 20-year warranty for quality. All-in-one? YES!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Do you need time to think? Don\u2019t worry\u2014<a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/contact-us\/\">start with a free consultation<\/a> and get a free estimate for your home!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Explore, More About <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/cool-summer-colors\/\">Cool Summer Colours<\/a><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Here are some popularly asked questions.<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>1. What are popular colour schemes for summer decor?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Popular colour schemes for summer decor include light and cool colours like white, blue, and pastels.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>2. How can I create light and airy spaces for summer?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>To create light and airy spaces for summer, use sheer curtains, minimal furniture, and light-coloured fabrics.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>3. Any budget-friendly tips for updating summer decor?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Budget-friendly tips for updating summer decor include adding fresh plants, swapping out heavy fabrics for lighter ones, and doing simple DIY projects.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>4. Which furniture and fabrics work best for summer?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Wicker or rattan furniture and breathable fabrics like cotton or linen work best for summer.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>5. What are the key elements of an inviting outdoor space for summer?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Comfortable seating, ambient lighting, and plenty of greenery are key elements of an inviting outdoor space for summer.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>6. What are some simple DIY projects for summer decor?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Simple DIY projects for summer decor include making seashell decorations, painting hanging pots, and creating summer wreaths.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>7. How can I integrate smart technology into my summer decor?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>You can integrate smart technology into your summer decor by using smart thermostats, automated blinds, and smart lighting.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<div class=\"row blog-form\">\n\t<div class=\"offset-lg-3 col-lg-6 bg-light\">\n<fieldset class=\"field-set\">\n<!-- <legend align=\"left\"> -->\n                    \n    <h3 class=\"widget-title text-dark text-center mb-0\">Looking For Functional Interior Designs?<\/h3>\n  \n \n     <p class=\"text-center text-dark mt-0\"> Get 20% extra space with smart solutions<\/p>\n    <!-- <\/legend> -->\n<form id=\"blogContactUsFormMain\" action=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/get_quote_action.php\" method=\"post\"\n    novalidate=\"novalidate\">\n    <div class=\"form-group\">\n        <input type=\"text\" class=\"form-control\"  name=\"your-name\" placeholder=\"Enter your name*\" \/>\n        <!-- <span class=\"sales-txt-label\" id=\"labeltxt\">Enter your name*<\/span>  -->\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"form-row dc-falg-row\">\n        <!-- <div class=\"form-group col-md-3 guideForm\">\n            <select name=\"your-phone-ext\" id=\"id_select2_example\" class=\"id_select2_example drop-downfield form-dropdown\"\n                onfocus='this.size=5;' onblur='this.size=1;' onchange='this.size=1; this.blur();'\n                data-width=\"100%\" data-minimum-results-for-search=\"Infinity\">\n               \n                <option value=\"+01\"\n                    data-img_src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/06163948\/01.png\">\n                    +01\n                <\/option>\n                <option value=\"+91\"\n                    data-img_src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/10\/06164015\/91.png\"\n                    selected>\n                    +91\n                <